Logical Operators

When we need to test for 2 or more conditions we use LOGICAL Operators

    AND OR NOT
    && || !

AND
true && true -> TRUE
true && false -> FALSE
false && true -> FALSE
false && false -> FALSE

boolean cold=true;
boolean rain=false;

if (cold && rain) { --> FALSE
        SOPln ("I will stay at home");
}

OR
true || true -> TRUE
true || false -> TRUE
false || true -> TRUE
false || false -> FALSE

if (cold || rain) { --> TRUE
    SOPln ("I will stay at home");
}

NOT - reverse the condition

    boolean boo=!false;
    System.out.println(boo); //true

Switch Statement -

syntax

switch (variable) {

case value1:
            code A;
            break;
case value2:
            code B;
            break;
default:
        Code C;
        break;
}




Loop